candidates.title: Update dependencies
candidates.body:
Most notably this updates `mdbook` to 0.4.48, which adds support for Rust 2024 edition in the mdbook configuration.

The new version on `svgbob` also removes a couple of unused configuration options, `enhance_circuitries` and `merge_line_with_shapes`.

candidates.body:

Release notes

Sourced from crossbeam-channel's releases.

crossbeam-channel 0.5.15

  • Fix regression introduced in 0.5.12 that can lead to a double free when dropping unbounded channel. (#1187)

crossbeam-channel 0.5.14

  • Fix stack overflow when sending large value to unbounded channel. (#1146, #1147)
  • Add Select::new_biased function. (#1150)
  • Remove inefficient spinning. (#1154)
  • Suppress buggy clippy::zero_repeat_side_effects lint in macro generated code. (#1123)

Changelog

Sourced from env_logger's changelog.

[0.11.5] - 2024-07-25

[0.11.4] - 2024-07-23

[0.11.3] - 2024-03-05

Features

  • Experimental support for key-value logging behind unstable-kv

[0.11.2] - 2024-02-13

[0.11.1] - 2024-01-27

Fixes

  • Allow styling with Target::Pipe

[0.11.0] - 2024-01-19

Migration Guide

env_logger::fmt::Style: The bespoke styling API, behind color, was removed, in favor of accepting any ANSI styled string and adapting it to the target stream's capabilities.

Possible styling libraries include:

  • anstyle is a minimal, runtime string styling API and is re-exported as env_logger::fmt::style
  • owo-colors is a feature rich runtime string styling API
  • color-print for feature-rich compile-time styling API

custom_format.rs uses anstyle via Formatter::default_level_style

Breaking Change

  • Removed bespoke styling API
    • env_logger::fmt::Formatter::style
    • env_logger::fmt::Formatter::default_styled_level
    • env_logger::fmt::Style
    • env_logger::fmt::Color
    • env_logger::fmt::StyledValue
  • Removed env_logger::filter in favor of env_filter

Compatibility

MSRV changed to 1.71

candidates.title: Fix build with mdbook >= 0.4.37
candidates.body:
- mdbook 0.4.37 pulls a new incompatible pulldown-cmark
- Use pulldown-cmark 0.10
- Use pulldown-cmark-to-cmark 14.0 for dependency match
- Adapt to the new API

candidates.title: Updated `proc-macro2` version to `1.0.67`
candidates.body:
This updates the version for dependency `proc-macro2` in Cargo.lock and removes required_version from .rustfmt.toml since we suspect the ci tests are failing because of it.

- Referred [this](https://stackoverflow.com/a/38615349)  for updating the dependency in Cargo.lock
- Removed the `required_version` in .rustfmt.toml as we are using the nightly version in the tests which will automatically use the latest version
- Changed [fn_args_layout](https://rust-lang.github.io/rustfmt/?version=v1.6.0&search=#fn_args_layout) to [fn_params_layout](https://rust-lang.github.io/rustfmt/?version=v1.6.0&search=#fn_params_layout) as it is deprecated.
